{{Infobox organization | formation = 1914 | purpose = [[Humanitarian Aid]] | headquarters = [[Luxembourg City]], [[Luxembourg]] | leader_title = President | leader_name = [[Maria Teresa, Grand Duchess of Luxembourg|Grand Duchess Maria Teresa]] | parent_organization = [[International Federation of Red Cross and Red Crescent Societies]] | volunteers = 15,000 (2013)<ref name="ifrcdata">{{Cite web|url=http://www.ifrc.org/data|title=IFRC Data Explorer}}</ref> | name = Luxembourg Red Cross | staff = 1,915 (2013)<ref name="ifrcdata">{{Cite web|url=http://www.ifrc.org/data|title=IFRC Data Explorer}}</ref> | region = [[Luxembourg]] | website = http://www.croix-rouge.lu/ | native_name = Croix-Rouge luxembourgeoise {{fr icon}}, Luxemburgische Rote Kreuz {{lb icon}} }}
The '''Luxembourg Red Cross''' ({{lang-fr|Croix-Rouge Luxembourgeoise}}, {{lang-de|Luxemburgische Rote Kreuz}}) is the [[Luxembourg]]-based [[List of Red Cross and Red Crescent Societies|National Society]] of the [[International Red Cross and Red Crescent Movement]]. The society was established on 8 August 1914 by Emile and Aline Mayrisch. They persuaded the mayor of [[Luxembourg City]], the commander-in-chief of the army and representatives of the three churches to sign the founding certificate. Its President is currently [[Maria Teresa, Grand Duchess of Luxembourg|Grand Duchess Maria Teresa]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ifrc.org/en/what-we-do/where-we-work/europe/luxembourg-red-cross/|title=Luxembourg Red Cross - IFRC|website=www.ifrc.org|access-date=2016-06-23}}</ref> Michel Simonis is the managing director.<ref name="Wort2">{{cite news|title=Former Luxembourg Red Cross director has died|url=http://www.wort.lu/en/luxembourg/remembering-jacques-hansen-former-luxembourg-red-cross-director-has-died-5795bcb2ac730ff4e7f6405f|accessdate=25 January 2017|publisher=Luxemburger Wort|date=25 July 2016}}</ref>
The Grand Duchess was the guest of honour at an event to celebrate the 20th anniversary of the Luxembourg Red Cross Bazaar in [[Limpertsberg]] in November 2016.<ref name="Wort">{{cite news|title=Grand Duchess heads bazaar 20th anniversary celebrations|url=http://www.wort.lu/en/panorama/luxembourg-red-cross-grand-duchess-heads-bazaar-20th-anniversary-celebrations-5831a1795061e01abe83c65b|accessdate=25 January 2017|publisher=Luxemburger Wort|date=20 November 2016}}</ref>
