'''William Clarence Braisted''' (9 October 1864 ‚Äì 17 January 1941) was an [[United States|American]] [[surgeon]]. He was born in [[Toledo, Ohio]], died at home in [[West Chester, Pennsylvania]], and is buried at [[Arlington National Cemetery]]. He graduated from the [[University of Michigan]] in 1883 and with [[Doctor of Medicine]] degree from the [[Columbia University College of Physicians and Surgeons]] in 1886. He was the [[Surgeon General of the United States Navy]] from 1914 to 1920 and the president of the [[American Medical Association]] from 1920 to 1921.<ref name="TheMilitarySurgeon">{{Cite journal |date=March 1943 |last=Roddis |first=Louis H. |title=William Clarence Braisted, Surgeon General of the Navy (1914-20) |journal=The Military Surgeon |volume=92 |pages=317‚Äì23 |url=https://archive.org/details/WilliamBraistedByLouisRoddis |access-date=2017-05-18}}</ref><ref name=JAMA>{{Cite journal |date=1919-06-21 |title=The President-Elect, Surgeon-General William C. Braisted |journal=Journal of the American Medical Association (JAMA) |volume=72 |issue=2 |page=1847 |url={{Google books|id=z_BGAQAAMAAJ|page=1847|plainurl=yes}} |access-date=2017-05-18}}</ref>

