'''«ÉXu''' is possibly the main god of the [[San people|San]] of southern [[Africa]]. He is considered a benevolent and omnipotent [[God|supreme being]].<ref>Richard Katz, Megan Biesele, Verna St. Denis. {{google books|id=z63kSi61TSwC|title=Healing Makes Our Hearts Happy: Spirituality and Cultural Transformation Among the Kalahari Ju\'hoansi|page=43}}</ref> He is also the sky god to whom the souls of the dead go. He is said to "Summon the magicians to their profession, and gives them supernatural powers." The San add that he provides the rain and is invoked in illness, before hunting and before traveling.

The deity is also known as !Xuba, !Xo or !Xoba.<ref>[[Dorothea Bleek|Dorothea F. Bleek]], {{Google books|id=l3UTAwAAQBAJ|title=Bushman Dictionary|page=502}}. {{ISBN|9785882327261}}</ref>

Xu, a [[List of geological features on Rhea#Craters|crater on Rhea]], the second largest moon of Saturn, is named after «ÉXu.<ref>{{cite web|title=Planetary Names: Crater, craters: Xu on Rhea|url=http://planetarynames.wr.usgs.gov/Feature/6618|website=Gazetteer of Planetary Nomenclature|publisher=[[International Astronomical Union]] (IAU) Working Group for Planetary System Nomenclature (WGPSN)|accessdate=20 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{google books|id=UYDph90f8PAC|title=The Compact NASA Atlas of the Solar System|page=401}} [[Cambridge University Press]], 2001. {{ISBN|9780521806336}}</ref>

